sentences.english: SCIENTISTS in Canada have found that picking your NOSE and eating it could be good for your health.

sentences.chinese: 原来他刚才在挖鼻孔，然后鼻屎现在到了我嘴里。

sentences.english: I leave run quickly, you dig nose excrement.
In fact, nose excrement is our good friend.

sentences.english: I 've got a booger stuck in my nose.

sentences.english: The movement of his lips caused the snot to fall right into my mouth.
sentences.chinese: 结果他说话的动作导致那鼻屎直接掉进了我嘴里。

sentences.english: All those years you told me not to eat my boogers?

sentences.english: When we feeling boring, we can to dig out nose excrement.

sentences.english: He laid the dry snotpickedfrom his nostril ledge of rock, carefully.

sentences.english: Looking up at his nose, I saw snot dripping.
sentences.chinese: 我抬头看着他的鼻子，发现有块鼻屎岌岌可危。
